<TITLE> Aide Tamim for greater e-governance </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 18 (bdnews24.com) - The chief adviser's special aide M Tamim has stressed the need for government officials to acquire better skills in use of information technology for wider implementation of e-governance. "Information can be transferred easily and quickly through electronic systems. If government services can be introduced through electronic systems and the internet the public will be better served," Tamim told a seminar on Saturday. "To that end, employees should be better skilled and equipped in using information technology," he said. The special aide said: "The chief adviser is also eager to take effective measures for the spread of science and technology in the country." Bangladesh Computer Council, Bangladesh Institute of Peace and Security Studies and Australian National University, Canberra organised the seminar titled 'E-governance in Bangladesh: Strategic ways of development' held at the Sheraton Hotel Saturday. bdnew
